If you ever need a clear-cut example of the Invisible Hand principle, look no further than Rwanda. Just a refresher – the theory was developed by the so-called father of economics, Adam Smith, who argued that man’s self-interest benefits society. In broader terms, Rwandan president Paul Kagame embodies this. The former military leader has brought peace and economic prosperity to a country scarred by the 1994 genocide. All he wants in return, very simplistically, is to rule with an iron fist. No dissidence, no challenges. It’s a simple trade-off. After Momentum this week became yet another major sponsor to demand...